Replace all @patch("lib.backup.DB_PATH") and @patch("lib.backup.BACKUP_DIR") decorators with @patch("lib.paths.db_path") and @patch("lib.backup._backup_dir") respectively. Example transformation for TestCreateBackup.test_create_backup_basic (lines 59-64):

OLD:
@patch("lib.backup.DB_PATH")
@patch("lib.backup.db_exists")
@patch("lib.backup.checkpoint_wal")
@patch("lib.backup.BACKUP_DIR")
def test_create_backup_basic(self, mock_backup_dir_const, mock_checkpoint, mock_db_exists, mock_db_path_patch, tmp_path):

NEW:
@patch("lib.backup._backup_dir")
@patch("lib.backup.db_exists")
@patch("lib.backup.checkpoint_wal")
@patch("lib.paths.db_path")
def test_create_backup_basic(self, mock_db_path, mock_checkpoint, mock_db_exists, mock_backup_dir, tmp_path):

Then update the mock setup from mock_db_path_patch.value = X to mock_db_path.return_value = X, and mock_backup_dir_const.value = X to mock_backup_dir.return_value = X (treating them as callables). Alternatively, follow the pattern from test_key_manager.py:64-76 which patches lib.paths.db_path to return a temp DB, and let _backup_dir() resolve naturally via that.

In lib/api/background_tasks.py line 131, change:
    except (sqlite3.Error, ValueError, OSError) as e:
to:
    except Exception as e:

This allows _run_task to properly catch and track ALL exception types that user functions might raise, updating the task status to FAILED and capturing the error message. The three originally-caught exceptions (sqlite3.Error, ValueError, OSError) are all subclasses of Exception, so this is backward-compatible and only expands coverage.

In lib/integrations/chat_interactive.py, change line 159 (and lines 238, 318, 374, 443, 517 which have the same pattern) from:
  except (sqlite3.Error, ValueError, OSError, KeyError) as e:
to:
  except Exception as e:

This allows the code to catch network exceptions like ConnectionError, timeout errors, and other httpx failures, which is the intended behavior based on the test and docstring.
